e medal table with 48 golds of their 100 medals that year.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1924, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999984285890219, \"rank\": 1.441358191000185e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1861}, {\"ngram\": \"a driver\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1883}, {\"ngram\": \"that investment\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal table\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"48 golds\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"their 100 medals\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Seven of those golds came in diving, as in fact 18 per cent of their all-time golds have - 49 out of 265 - but they fell one short of the clean sweep again.\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those golds\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2018}, {\"ngram\": \"diving\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2045}, {\"ngram\": \"18 per cent\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2057}, {\"ngram\": \"their all-time golds\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"the clean sweep\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2147}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I would have loved to have trained with them at one point, and been able to actually go out to China and dive alongside them,\\\" Laugher added.\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2252, \"end\": 2257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999984285890219, \"rank\": 1.441358191000185e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one point\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2214}, {\"ngram\": \"Lau